<h1><span id="Alapin.27s_Opening"></span><span id="Alapin's_Opening">Alapin's Opening</span></h1>
<h2><span id="2._Ne2">2. Ne2</span></h2>
<p>An uncommon move that initially blocks White's bishop on f1, the idea however is often to play f4 a sort of King's Gambit but without the idea of giving up the f-pawn.
Play could transpose into a Scotch Game if Black replies 2...Nc6
</p><p><b>1. e4 e5 2. Ne2</b>
</p>
